President Obama expresses his sadness over the passing of Reverend Fred Shuttlesworth, a civil rights leader and co-founder of the Southern Christian Leadership Conference. He acknowledges Shuttlesworth's dedication to advancing justice for all Americans and recognizes him as a symbol of the strength of the human spirit. The President also recalls the opportunity he had to push Shuttlesworth in his wheelchair across the Edmund Pettus Bridge, a powerful symbol of the sacrifices made for equality. Obama concludes by expressing America's gratitude towards Shuttlesworth and offering thoughts and prayers to his family and loved ones.